caption: Service was prompt and food was great as usual, but drinks were terrible. Come here often and the bartender was someone we didn't recognize when we walked in, she seemed nice though. Definitely needs some work. Couple of old fashioned we order for the table were way too sweet. Embarrassing as we'd invited friends and were sadly disappointed.
Super chill environment!! Had a really tasty salmon plate with a margarita. It definitely hit the spot 👍
Great food! Great service!
It was closed when we went by. So I didn't get a chance to really experience it.
Matt, one of the late night cooks, came thru clutch and provided excellent customer service. Makes a mean burger too
Ordered the lamb gyro and Bleu Idaho steak salad and both were very tasty!! French fries were very good too! Highly recommend this place!!!
Good place to get lunch and awesome atmosphere
Yum yum
Was my first time in and really enjoyed the food an service. Everyyrhing came out warm and the seasonal cheesecake we got was to die for. Will be back.
We ordered our food to go and it was so delicious when we got home!!! Definitely will order from/eat here again!! Thanks Solid!
Open mic and more.

I've been coming here for 11 years. The food has always been great. Service has been good, every time, for the most part. I'll continue to come here. It has a great atmosphere, a good crowd and a great menu. I miss the breakfast menu tho.... 😥
Horrible service and terrible food.
Very good food and drinks. Cauliflower Bombs are da bomb, chicken cordon blue, and herb chicken were both great entrees.
Great place to visit in Boise, could use some heavier drink pours but overall friendly service and good times
Great prices!  Burger and sweet potato fries are yummy!
Been eating here for 7 years. Theres a good reason. Kitchen is on point.
Opened late. Staff is fabulous!
Grat atmosphere, Aly is so awesome, great musician and singer! Food was fabulous!
We keep returning here for their varied, tasty menu, and the location. Love being able to sit on the patio with some live music (usually just someone with a guitar signing, not too loud).
Creative vegan and gluten free menu items! Excellent patio.

Went for drinks late on Monday night, had a fantastic time. The drinks were relatively well priced, I ended up trying something i didnt like and the bartender (Justin I believe) took care of us and got us something same comparable price that I knew I would enjoy. He was professional, friendly, and great service. Ive always loved the solid for their tacos, but I will also return for their cocktails, taps, and interesting house specials😊
Outdoor dining, live music, varied menu, tasty drinks. What's not to like?

Sadly, they revised their menu and removed amazing options: the menage a trois bread plate and vegan mushroom street tacos. Tried their pita/hummus and new version of the vegan street tacos. It was not a good time. Hummus was chunky and tempeh on the street tacos was a weird combo. Definitely not going back unless they bring back the old options.

Really tasty chicken, vegetables, and risotto. Would definitely go back here to get it. Mojito was also very good.  The best thing about this place IMO is the patio seating with live music. This was the first place I went to after getting to Boise, and I loved the vibe of the city.
Food is excellent!  Get the BLT.
The BlackJack Burger paired with Split Rail Syrah (Idaho wine) is a damn near perfect pairing..

I arrived while a customer was belligerent about wearing a mask. I was there for a pickup order and they handled the situation very well. They moved arriving customers to a place where they didnt have to witness the customer who was causing trouble. The manager on staff sounded very professional in their talk with that customer and handled the situation well. They got food out fairly quick, and had nice, clean surroundings!!
Great food! Great cocktail menu! Live music during the week and for Sunday Brunch! Definitely will return!
Food A+, drinks A+, service can be shotty from time to time.  Had awesome servers and also those who were having a BAD day. Otherwise, awesome place.
Wonderful live music and delicious nachos. The misters on the patio were perfect
Our experience was great here. Our waiter was helpful and friendly. Had a great salad selection and the gyro was excellent.
Great atmosphere, finominal food that met requirements for both a gluten free order and a vegetarian order. We were super happy with our service and order.

Happy hour was great, but there was a bit of a wait even though Solid wasn't very busy. The beer selection was good (almost all local) and very well priced. Wine selection was also good. The nachos are are huge and a great night time snack for 4 people.
Good ambience with the live music, and the food was better than expected. Good value
Hannah is the world’s greatest host/server! She is the reason we keep coming back. Great jalapeño margarita!
Great food, great atmosphere, and i loved the live music it was a breath of fresh air in these crazy times

The food was good, the service was good, social distancing requirements were observed, everyone wore a mask, and it was comfortable in there even though it was super hot outside. Also this place boasts two outside patios which are really nice when they are running the misters. For some reason on this day the misters were not running but it probably had something to do with low customer volume at that time.
They have  nice outdoor seating with live music.

I waiting 10 mins for a waitress to take my order but after that my drinks came quick and I love the live entertainment.  The bar tender comped my meal and drinks due to the wait we had at the beginning which was amazing! It goes to show that they really take care of their customers.

Just sat outside for 23 minutes, not even offered water after being noticed 3 times. With a group of service industry friends who would have loved to have ordered lunch and tip well had we even been acknowledged.

First time in Boise and first time at solid. Corey was our server and you could tell he was swamped. Over hearing a conversation, he was the only server on that night because of a sick call, with what I could see about 15 tables he was doing on his own. Food was great and even tho Corey was slammed he killed it and stayed kind and courteous the entire time. When we come back to Boise we will come back to solid mainly because Corey was a stud, but, food was awesome as well!

Corey A was exceptional! Rocked it being rhe only server on staff and made this bartender/Server put of Washington State  very happy! Thank you for making a very long drive worth it at the end of the day!
Good food and beer selection.
The wings were meaty and delicious and their house BBQ sauce is amazing.

had such a wonderful experience here! the hostess/server Rose was attentive, friendly, and knowledgeable. I hope I see her the next time i’m back here! She recommended the risotto balls and they are to die for!!
This was the driest burger I have ever had. Even our kid wouldn't touch the pasta.
Solidly good food!
Good food and drinks reasonably priced. The happy hours are from 4 to 6 and 10 to midnight. Cozy patio seating with live music, Several local beers on tap.
Very tasty nachos and open late!
Love it!!!!
Excellent venue right downtown. Open space the tables are well spread out and the building is a restored old building with the a lot of character
Good burger and beers
Nice vibe. Lots of vegan and vegetarian options.  Reasonably priced.
Perfect patio.
We went here and had lunch outside and felt very safe during these covid times. I really like solid and wasn't disappointed. The food and service were great.
Great food... fantastic service!!
Nice place. Good music on the patio.

What a welcome surprise for the evening.  Had planned on going to another establishment in the area to find the employees were not wearing masks to protect their patrons. Looked at other businesses in the area  that too were not protecting others.  Found  Solid and we were extremely pleased they were wearing masks, had a great menu and the food did not disappoint, even had GF options which I struggle  to find at times. Definitely recommend and will be back!
Great atmosphere and friendly staff. The cauliflower wings were really tasty!
Live music today because it matters
Lunch on the patio was awesome again!
Nice place. Good people and service. Patio is very nice, and musical.
These guys have THE BEST Eggs Benedict I have ever tasted! Fun, cozy dining and outdoor seating as well
Drinks and food were tasty.  Took away 1 star because the beers we wanted were not available.
Friendly bar staff. Good prices. Open for late nite food
Solid experience
Great food
Plenty of food, excellent quality, great atmosphere definitely going back.
FRANKIE is the reason my Sister Talya and I cant get enough of this place!! Great booze and an amazing atmosphere! Every night is SOLID! LOL
Good food. Nice atmasphere.
Great hamburger well worth the money.
Great food
Best pizza downtown!!! Hands down!!

I love this place!  I've had a club sandwich and an amazing burger.  Both times I had their sweet potato fries, and those things are phenomenal.  I'm also so about the ice water with sliced cucumber.  So refreshing!  Oh and did I mention they are VERY reasonably priced?
I had the uncle buck which is a burger with grilled cheese sandwiches as buns. My gf had the chicken and waffles and says its the best shes ever had.
The service is friendly and the food is really good. My blackened steak was cooked perfectly and the portions are large. It was too spicy for me and they were very helpful in making our meal perfect.

First the food was amazing, but we wanted a nice night out for Valentine’s Day but our waiter Matt seemed as if he couldn’t care less about us being there and paid no attention  to us and very rarely checked on us but checked on the group next to us quite a bit and conversed with them but when it came to us he barely spoke and he was quick to leave and we just wanted to leave and getting the check and our boxes took a very long time, he really made us feel unwelcome and uncomfortable I would recommend the food but the service was the worst I’ve ever had.
Food and apps are always good, service is great, good spot in Bodo for dropping in mid day and prices are very much reasonable.

My husband and I ate at the Solid yesterday afternoon. The waiter was nice, but after we had ordered I saw him wipe his nose with his thumb and forefinger.  He still had to deliver our meals. I wanted to walk out. I cannot get this off my mind and shall never return. We ordered the sweet potato enchilada and the kimchi fries. Ugh!
Service was good. I had the Doc Hudson burger. It was pretty good, but the fries had room for improvement. All in all, I'd say it was pretty Solid...

The Solid is a must stop every time we make a trip to Boise.  We always stay at the Grove and this place is right around the corner.  They have great spinach dip and they're defibrillator is something to experience.

We went here to celebrate my sister's birthday.  Our server acted like we were bothering him or annoying him. Also they forgot one person's order and she had to wait for her food after the rest of us were completely finished.  Our server did correct the order error but had no apologies. Decent food but horrible service. I would NOT recommend this place at all.
Good food and great service comfortable atmosphere. Lots to choose from at a decent reasonable price.
Blackened salmon was delicious! Good value for the food, staff were polite.

The Pear and Goat cheese salad was killer (I added blue cheese dressing on the side) Chicken Cordon Bleu was very good, crispy and the sauce was excellent, paired with great Garlic Mashed Potatoes and al dente asparagus.  Excellent meal over all and very friendly service.  We went at 2 in the afternoon and two adults split the large salad and chicken and we had a child's dish as well, all for under $40!
Vegan options are great & highly recommend the peanut butter beer!
The burgers are great.
Really good food and drinks! Servers were very pleasant.  :)
The steak is nice n juicy.  He loves the chicken strips n fresh fries.
Good food and drinks, our waiter wasn't very personable unfortunately.
Great place. A huge variety of food options. Everything from gyros to chicken and waffles. Also, the guns and oil lager is great in name and taste!
Good food and recently upgraded facility. 7ft Diamond tabels in Great shape...
It was fine. Service and drinks were good! Food was fine. Not worth the cost.
The chicken quesadilla is amazing! And so is this local blackberry cider. My server (I think her name was Star) was really nice and gave great service. All around highly recommended!
Great food, good drinks!

My wife and I really love to come downtown to have breakfast or brunch.  I am conflicted in letting people know about solids sunday mornings.  All my other favorite spots are overly crowded.  The food is wonderful, drinks are high quality, service is friendly and quick.  I was impressed.
The food is always incredible and the service is great.  We had a wonderful guitar player throughout our dinner.
Love their shrimp and grits!
The chicken did not have strong flavor.  However, the Risotto was delicious. I also had the Clam Chowder, it was thick and delicious. the service was good.
Shrimp and grits is just what you need on a cold winter evening!
Fresh Cut Fries!!!! And open super late! Had an hour to kill at the parking lot to pay after seeing a showIf anything just those are worth coming. Atmosphere is unique and food is decent.

Loved my shrimp & grits the  last time I visited.  Decided to visit again for lunch.  To their defense it was dead because it was 2.  Our server was absolutely darling & fantastic.  However,  the food was disappointing to me. My chicken in my soup was rubber.  My salad was great but my entree just needed some enchilada sauce.  I ordered gfree sweet potato enchilada. Great idea, needs enchilada sauce.  The quinoi salad is a great idea.  Not sure too many  people would enjoy but good thought.  My husband ordered Kimchi fries. I guess they were so dry he would not even take them home to my kids.   We will come back but please pay attention to the main ingredients in your food & make sure they are cooked correctly.   We rarely get to have lunch together so a little sad that it wasn't fantastic.  Please visit this restaurant, I am confident all the non gluten free is amazing!!!
Good food, and nice atmosphere. The staff was friendly and did a great job!

Loved this place. I visited here from Molalla, OR and happened upon this place. Very good prices on made from scratch items. Everything is made fresh in house. Between my two friends and me we had blueberry mojito, thai basil martini, a jalepeno/cucumber beverage and craft beers. I had street tacos and chips with guacamole and salsa, again ALL made from scratch while they had chowder and a BLT with hand cut fries (yum!). Would recommend this place and can't wait to return and try other fresh entrees.
Radical!
Excellent experience! The food was very much more than merely "solid"... it was fantastic. The server was very friendly and professional.  I would definitely stop in again when I'm in Boise.
Solid
Good atmosphere, appropriate pricing, good food.

Waited 10 min before being waited on... waited another 10-15 min on drinks. Then waited 45 min for food... was not happy... they weren't even busy it was empty. Shouldn't have to wait that long especially when noone else was there... wont go there again that's for sure!!!

Experiences may vary. But it was 20 mins to get a small soda that was $3, another 10 mins to get a straw and over an hour for the food. Other plates looked good but the french dip i ordered was very underwhelming. Expect better for a place like this.
Cool place to get some food and a drink
Great mimosas and food.
Great Service, food, and drinks. Fantastic patio with live music in the summer.

The bartenders here know how to make you feel at home! They always have a smile and are egar to please. I’m new to the Boise  area and I can honestly say THIS is my FAVE spot thus far! There’s a really adorable bartender... he’s bald and his name is Mikey... such a friendly guy and makes the perfect drink every time! Definitely be back 10/10.
Really liked the bartender. Food was good, just didn't care for how they dressed their gyro.

My husband & I stopped in for dinner before heading to a show at the knitting factory && we were completely happy with our experience! Our Food was delicious, the staff was awesome! The best steak salad I have eaten in a long time!! We will absolutely return!
Amazing menu!! Bread Pudding... to die for!

Good food. Good beer. Live music. Good service. I really can't say anything bad about this place. There was 4 of us and everyone enjoyed their meals. We had the kimchee fries, spinach and artichoke dip, inferno and hot wings, some kind of burger with tempura bacon on it, nachos, and enchiladas. The only complaint from anyone was that the wasn't enough chicken on the nachos. All in all, very good.
I had the Seoul Burger and it was amazing. Great price for large portions and amazing fries.
Really nice spot. Great food, drink, and artwork from Ed Anderson Art

If you can help it- don’t support this establishment. Never have been so disrespected as a customer. Salsa Dancing “instructor” is arrogant as can be. Bald bartender is a close second. We’ll never go back. Very unfortunate.
They have patio dining, happy hour, good food
Ordered take out here late at night after arriving in Boise late in the evening. For “late night eats” it was delicious. Recommend the herb roasted chicken. A Solid choice.
Love this place. The food is always great.
The best food place
Big portions and friendly staff
Had to wait a little for my meal but the steak was cooked perfectly, so well worth it. Also the live patio music made a very pleasant atmosphere to relax in.
Excellent food and drinks
Frankie makes the best drinks in town
Delicious!
The herb chicken is excellent!

I really love going into this restaurant, the menu is big enough to please a party, yet small enough to not be overwhelmed with options. I found my go to meal while eating there and that is the Soule Burger. Who knew kimchi and ground beef would get along so well with your taste buds. The serving staff have always been very great and on their game. When friends come in from out of town that is first place I take them and on more than one occasion I've gotten a message to remind them what the name of the place was (I guess solid is a hard word to remember), so they can tell their friends about this necessary destination.
Good food, drinks, atmosphere, and friendly staff
Love the street tacos and outdoor music!
Place full of shady people one of the cooks is a Predator so as long as James isn’t working I take this is it OK please

By far my favorite bar in downtown Boise. Spent many weekends sitting on the patio listening to live music and sipping on Old Fashion. Something about their Old Fashion tastes much better than anywhere I've had it. Must be the ice balls they use!

Food- Fresh, good Sources, Yummy taste, good Variation of styles and diet choices, Drinks: Full bar,  No hot Sake😫 Other: Happy Accomodating Staff. Mid to high range Prices. Great Atmosphere, View, Airflow & Light.  Entertainment: LOVE him, completely love him, went back & was so happy he was there... and then I swayed under the tree on the park bench in the city and listened,  breathing with His hands. 🌴  Extra, not needed information: I have only visited twice so far.   The first time it was lunch and I was starving.  We sat at a table pushed up against the wall with clean plush pillows on the booth side.  The outside patio was visable 0⁰ from the large open windows next to us.  My son peeked through watching mostly locals chatting while the guitarist strummed an enchanting Zeppelin weave.

Such a perfect place to eat/Drink, Night or day! Family atmosphere in the day and night best place to relax for a drink after work. Highly recommend you come in on the hours that Mikey/Frankie are bartending. BEST DRINKS AROUND. Especially when you ask them to make you something special, THEY MAKE IT PERFECT.  Hope everyone makes the time to come check out this hidden treasure in our Treasure Valley area. THEY EVEN HAVE LIVE MUSIC WITH LOCAL ARTIST>> SO again, I highly recommend this place. 5 stars, I would do more if I could!
Me and my wife had the chicken coursing blue tonight and I puked and she is still puking right now. Don’t ever order it!  Solid became liquid puke!
Excellent food.  Friendly service.  Convenient walk from our hotel.
Cocktail waitress on Mon night made a great Old Fashion, but it's more of a simple drink establishment when she isn't working.  Steak salad very good.
This has to be my favorite place in Boise! I have tried several things there and always have to come back for more!

I usually visit restaurants the second I see a "vegan" option.  I was absolutely surprised when my partner suggested we come to this bar for a quick drink and a meal.  They had a really unique veggie burger and amazing fries.  I absolutely suggest the fries, we also got a bread appetizer for starters that had spreads with it.  I honestly had to hold myself back from ordering a second one!  The drink mixes were unique and very flavorful, and the atmosphere is what really sold the place.  Live music performed by a very talented musician had me singing along happily with what they were playing while I ate in a soft window.  So worth the visit!
The atmosphere was very inviting and the live entertainment was exceptional. Very handicap accessible. The food was very yummy and the price was reasonable.
The food was good, but the kitchen was especially slow for the place being as empty as it was at 4pm. They messed up my order but did fix it right away.

One of my favorite places to grab lunch!  Love the space and the ambiance and the excellent food as well.  The entire staff is friendly and the service is great.  Try the quesadillas...they're amazing!
This place is delicious. Their risotto balls are especially good. I'm always confused why this place isn't more crowded. Usually I go for their burgers.
Sunday morning bottomless mimosas are where it's at!
This place is one we stumbled upon and we dont regret it. Drinks and food prices were amazing plus I've never had such great service or food. Definitely a great recommendation

We ordered the monte hamburger and it was good. The bacon tasted smoked. The burger was cook perfect. The waiter was nice, did his job and even took care of us on the bill. My order was a little wrong no big deal though. The service and atmosphere is different. The  restaurant must be the local hipsters hang out which doesn’t matter other than the fact my family and I felt completely out of place.
Good food, but I found out when I got my bill that 2 for one happy hour only meant a limited menu, so I paid double what I was expecting.
We order burgers and they were great. But the server was rude and didn't know how to do his job with smile!
Croquet Madam breakfast is Amazing!!!
Good pasta
Seemed busy talking, waiting 20 minutes for a menu. Wednesday evening at 9. Won’t be back
Seriously be was slow on a Wednesday night, food just sub par. Not worth my time or money.

Maybe I ordered poorly? The black bean enchiladas were scrawny, overpriced and mediocre at best and the accompanying spicy risotto was an unidentifiable mostly inedible Southwest-ish mess.  However, the nachos were very generously heaped with toppings and the risotto bites were good (although a bit expensive) as well.  The mac and cheese was bland and also seemed to be pricey for what was served.  Cocktails were very good and beer selection is ample as well.  I see a lot of potential here and the menu lists many items I would like to try- I am just hoping that our last meal was a one-off fluke.
A good choice for visitors to Boise. Puts you in bodo, it's unique, the food is great, and the drink options are great too! (Trying really hard to not use the word solid)
Great wine selection, super good food. Great selection, many vegan options and meat eater options as well. Drop in and say hi to Kat, she'll treat you well.
Great service and great food
Great atmosphere! Always helpful staff. The salsa Dancing on Wednesdays creates a fun vibe for anyone at the bar. And their vegetarian options are numerous
The rissoto balls were amazing! Highly recommend. The service was great, and the server gave good suggestion for local nightlife attractions.
Delightful!
The food was good, it came in a decent amount for the price we paid. The seasonal cheeseburger was delicious!

Really, really good Italian Grinder and Herb Roasted Chicken, along with such a good rissoto and perfectly cooked veggies. Great service from Michael. Enjoyed a nice early dinner/late lunch today. Thank you!

Decided to go here after seeing an event of "Bottomless mimosas" on Facebook. Went right at 11am and it was not busy at all. Staff  was attentive and friendly. The mimosa bar had a variety of fruits and berries. I also thought the juices or champagne should have been chilled more. They were room temperature when we drank them. My friends and I had around 5 mimosas, so the price of $14 was worth it. Overall, I would recommend checking them out for a fun brunch date!
Fun place for Sunday brunch and all you can drink mimosas
Salmon fillet was excellent.  We could get in here when the other restaurants had long wait times
Always dependable for awesome daily specials as well as regular menu items-unique fare but not too bizarre, at reasonable prices
Me shopko with 4 kids for lunch. They were ap accommodating and accepting. We went during a non-peak time.
Been here a couple times, and I am sure to be back. Food is wonderful, service staff and atmosphere are extraordinary.
Had an amazing time celebrating my Birthday here! Very accommodating, good drinks and food. Calyse was our fantastic server!

Overall disappointing experience. We were there celebrating a friend’s birthday. There was no celebration at all on behalf of the restaurant. Our server and the hostess were both told that there was a birthday. My husband ordered a signature cocktail off the menu, which was a take on an Irish coffee. The drink came with just a cinnamon tequila and coffee... he took the drink to the bar to get it corrected, where the bartender argued with him about what was in the drink. He then had to look at the menu to make the drink correctly. The server then also argued about what was in the drink and left the table to check the menu! He came back and said it was a new menu and so he wasn’t familiar. No apologies, nothing. We were then charged an 18% automatic gratuity for only 7 people. To top it off, the food was all very mediocre. We will not be returning.

Came here because PF Changs had an hour wait. I was extremely dissapointed with the food, and service. There were four of us and we all thought is was not a pleasent experience. The server was not friendly, the food was not worth paying for at any price. Spinach artichoke dip was extremely bland and more cheesy than anything else. The chicken in my chicken and waffles was burnt so bad i couldn't eat the skin at all. Major bummer.
Great happy hour, amazing food & a good amount of vegan options!
Solid is amazing! Great quality food and drinks. My server Kat is is awesome! On top of her game. Go in and see her, she will make your experience awesome!
Always friendly staff and great food!
Delicious! I love their portabello sandwich! Lots of vegan choices.

This place is great! We rolled in at about midnight to try to get some food.  Only 1 guy running the place and he kept up with a crowd that started to grow as the Metallica concert in town ended.   Food was really good.
Had a great time with the attractive youths of Boise.  Very nice place and skilled bartender.
We were in a hurry, and the staff did an excellent job getting us in and out quickly. Food was great, as usual

Its a nice location and the food is good but the service was terrible. I met a friend at 1:00 for lunch on a Wednesday and there were only  4 tables with customers including us. It took 35 minutes to get a salad and a quesadilla. Waitress was scarce, and had to wait 10 minutes just to find her for our check. Hopefully they were just understaffed.
We were told that we were too old... not the kind of people they wanted on a Tuesday night. Bummer.
Great dinners
Steack not very tasty
First time to eat at Solid. I like the nice laid back atmosphere and their Dine Out Downtown Boise menu was delicious!!
Our waiter was amazing, and they put up with our semi large group. Nachos were fantastic
Very good food and drinks, but Kimchi  French Fries we're underwhelming.
Best shrimp n' Grits in town
Absolutely loved the Ham and bean soup.
The food and atmosphere we're both amazing. The kids menu was a hit with the littles.
Great staff, amazing burgers
Great food great people.  They made us feel at home.
Great food nice atmosphere, food portions may be a bit large but who complains about that?
Yummy wings
Lunch on their patio is one of the best in Boise!

Amazing food! Especially for vegetarians! Their risotto bites and the pear gorgonzola pizza are to die for while the portabello sandwich was amazing! Live music on a Tuesday night was perfect too. Plus the service was fantastic! Seriously what a great place!!
Great happy hour specials, perfect outdoor seating with excellent live music performances. One of our favorite places.
I love this place! The food and atmosphere are awesome.
Nice place, good service
Open late! Perfect for our late arrival in town. Interesting yet great food. Nice patio.
(Translated by Google) Very tasty food, good service  (Original) Comida muy rica, buena atención
Decent service. Underwhelmed by food quality.
The brunch was great. Always go with the bottom less mamosa!
Best food  wine, cocktails and music. Great ambiance
I come here for the swing dancing classes, however the food is also great!
Lovely place,  great food, seevice, and music.. Awesome prices for Boise. Will be back next year.

I love Solid Grill & Bar! Very open space, yet creates a cozy and fun environment. Love the gorgeous, unique glass lighting... Food is always delicious, wide variety of local spirits and fun concoctions tool drink... staff have always been welcoming and provided great service! Plus, they offer live music, social events like swing dance classes, varying specials and an awesome Happy Hour!
Incredibly rude, and disrespectful people. Terrible customer service. Beers were flat and refused to check carbonation. Nothing but positive experiences outside of this place.

It took us 30 minutes after getting seated to just to get water and someone to even acknowledge we were ready to order. Once our food did arrive about an hour after being seated, I was pleasantly surprised with the quality of the food. Although the service was slow, the live music was nice and the water misters were great for keeping the area comfortable and the food was good. I might consider going here again sometime.
Good music, good food, good service

Great food, but horrific experience with the server, who wasn't able to keep track of and split up our table's checks. It took us an hour or more to get out of there, with toddlers and little apologies.

The hamburgers are the best I have had out here so far. I highly recommend this place. I had the Old Doc Hudson and the onion rings. The onion are just okay  the the burger was amazing. They do get your food out you kinda fast which was nice. They do have live music as well on the patio.
Good place... lovely staff and music.
Wine platter is very tasty!
Great happy hour, half off and good food
Love the evening live  music
The Street Tacos are amazing! We especially come here because they have a pet friendly patio!!!
The bartender, Heather is amazing!!!!!!!!
Great food!
Great food & drinks!! Atmosphere & staff was fun!
Horrible service and my wife and I feel terrible after eating at this establishment.
Place was kind of dirty, and the help, while not rude, were not very friendly.

Everytime I have gone here something has been wrong with the orders. Last time there was mold on our bread. The food is good however and they are always willing to fix the problems. Fantastic cocktails
The Sunday Bruch was great and the service at the bar was excellent.

Awesome Spot! Our waitress Skyla was awesome and had a great knowledge of the menu...and an equally fantastic sense of humor.  The food is fresh and some ingredients are even made in house, as are some breads and all the desserts.  This is the kind of place you go because it's comfortable. Will definitely be heading back soon. Also the onion rings are awesome which would give any restaurant a 5 star review right?
Good stuff
Took an hour  and half to get food
Amazing food Everytime
Good place for drinks. Havent tried food but had an interesting menu.
Love the food and outdoor seating!

Good things happen when you meet strangers-- Yo-Yo Ma.  This is the 124th Yelp review for Solid Grill and Bar, downtown Boise, next to Liquid (fitting), the Knitting Factory, and much more! This is my 426th review on Yelp.  I've been here three times and each time I had a 5-star experience.  This particular visit was led by fate as was who I was with. The quote above is, in essence, my motto for YELP and sets the tone for this review.  After a yelp event, My Yelp friend turned real-life friend Chanda and her friend went looking for a place to eat.  Someone saw us walking by and suggested that we eat at Solid. I am so glad we did!  We walked in and were seated on the patio. There we saw my Yelpie Dani (again, good things happen when you meet strangers, right), and her dining companion. The music was so beautiful and I quickly realized that it was a person singing LIVE! What a treat!  The food was super good as well. I got the Portabello burger (mushroom in place of meat) with onion rings. My dining companions got risotto bites and a hummus platter. A full bar with a bartender that knows how to mix a drink, reasonable prices (especially for the location) and a superb atmosphere!  Then our Yelp ambassador here in Boise, Amie, walked in, with her beautiful smile! All these friendly strangers eating at the same place seems like a touch of fate to me, or perhaps a few shots of coincidence and technology, but I choose fate. What do you chose?
